    &lt;Title&gt;Amazing Team&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;J Howard&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I recently visited the Daisy Centre Day surgery for a gallbladder removal procedure, to say I was terrified was an understatement.  On arrival the staff were amazing, the nurses put me at ease straight away, the anaesthetist listened to my concerns as I had suffered a previous bad experience, he assured me he would look after me and do everything he could to avoid a repeat, this worked and I woke up a lot better with no sickness or shaking, I was also allowed to go home that day. To sum up, the experience was excellent and everyone was kind and friendly, nothing was too much trouble, everything was very well explained, I left with all the after care information I required which I referred to several times. 
I did not meet the surgeon but he did a good job too. 
Thank you to you all at the Daisy Centre day surgery, I could not have been better treated if I had paid private.  
&lt;/CommentText&gt;
